This code contains:
3 categories:
Electronics, Furniture, Groceries
Method 1 (fillInventory):
Asks the user to enter stock for 5 items in each category
If a negative number is entered → it automatically becomes 0
Method 2 (checkRestock):
Checks the stock and returns a status:
Above 10 → "Healthy"
5 to 10 → "Warning"
1 to 4 → "Critical"
0 → "Out of Stock"
Method 3 (calculateTotalStock):
Adds up all items and returns the total stock
Main Method:
Calls all the methods
Prints the result in grid format like:
Electronics: [Item1: 15 - Healthy] [Item2: 3 - Critical] ...
Total Warehouse Stock: 75
Basically it's a warehouse inventory system that tracks stock levels! 
